						<summary>

						<p>This is built in at the begining of each line and is also damaged. It seems to record a gift of money made by a lady for (special) offerings and worship in the temple on the day of Viśākha in Vaiśākha month. It gives also a list of some gold ornaments set with precious stones presented by the same donor, including a goldhandled fly-whisk and a silver salver.</p>						

						</summary>
